</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-24_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Paediatric first aid stands as a cornerstone in child safety, designed to offer immediate care until professional help arrives. Data from the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) underscore the prevalence of accidents in homes and schools, many of which could be lessened or managed better with basic first aid knowledge. The Resuscitation Council (UK) emphasises the importance of prompt and effective first aid responses, which can be crucial in saving a child's life during emergencies such as choking, drowning, or sudden cardiac arrest.



<br>
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-26_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-27_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-28_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-30_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-31_ pf-text-1"><strong>Paediatric first aid </strong>- Medical assistance provided to an ill or injured child, involving practices adapted to their specific physiological needs.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>Basic life support (BLS) </strong>- Critical care techniques utilised in life-threatening situations before full medical treatment is available.










