<br>
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>Immediate response</strong> - Quick and accurate assessment of the emergency situation to provide necessary care.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>CPR techniques</strong> - Tailored cardiopulmonary resuscitation methods for infants and children, recognising their unique anatomical and physiological differences.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-46_ pf-text-1"><strong>Handling choking</strong> - Effective strategies to manage choking, a common emergency in children under 5.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-48_ pf-text-1"><strong>Managing injuries</strong> - Proper care for frequent injuries in children such as burns, cuts, and bone fractures.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Prevention strategies</strong> - Training also focuses on preventive practices to reduce the risk of common accidents.











</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-52_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-53_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-54_ pf-heading-1-h3">Implementing what you learn</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-56_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Practical application through hands-on training is crucial. The British Heart Foundation advocates for regular practice of first aid techniques to ensure skills remain sharp and response times quick. It’s also recommended to attend refresher courses to keep abreast of the latest first aid protocols and techniques.


<br>
